    "Identified risks necessitate implementation of reasonable and proportionate mitigation measures.These risk assessments and mitigations will be subject to annual independent audits by accredited bodies assessing procedural compliance.",
    "Audit summaries containing key findings and recommendations must be publicly released.",
    "Ps may face significant fines for systematic failures in risk management amounting to up to 6% of global turnover.Other enhanced due diligence duties for VLOPs include additional obligations related to identity verification for advertisers, as well as vetting of platform policies by external experts to identify inconsistencies with the DSA's requirements.Overall, major platforms will need large investments in product redesign, content review, risk analysis, transparency systems and oversight mechanisms to meet the DSA's extensive accountability expectations applicable to very large entities.",
    "The costs for smaller competitors will be much lower.",
    "Policy context and timelineThe DSA emerged from rising concerns about online harms enabled through the design and use of digital platforms, and the limits of previous self-regulatory initiatives like the Code of Practice on Disinformation."
